      • uploadFile

        public void uploadFile(java.lang.String fileName,
              byte[] fileContent,
              java.lang.String fileDescription,
              java.lang.String[] fileTags,
              java.lang.String[] groupArray)
                throws java.io.IOException,
                       org.json.JSONException
        Upload a file to the APICA LoadTest Portal. Alreday existing files with the same file name will be recplaced / updated. Note: only some file types are allowed for upload - see VALID_UPLOAD_FILE_EXTENSIONS.
        Parameters:
        fileTags - the new tags for the file. null = do not modify tags, empty array = remove all tags
        groupArray -
        fileName - the file name
        fileContent - the content of the file
        fileDescription - an optional description about the file. This can also be null or be an empty string.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        org.json.JSONException
        See Also:
        VALID_UPLOAD_FILE_EXTENSIONS
